name: V Krishnapriya
about_me: An 18 year old computer science student, waiting for that ever-elusive freedom  and independence which I believe will come with money, clich√©d though it sounds. Also an introvert and book-lover. Life plans- get rich and backpack around the world with me,myself and I. Backup plan-become a librarian. I like playing all sports, listening to rock and instrumental music, and Batman.
why_ie: Though I am confused now by which technical events map to which club, its the people in IE who make me want to be a part of it. It appears that IE is a common ground for members of the other nontechnical clubs in college, such as the music club, artists forum and LSD. And to want to be able to regularly interact with such a diverse and talented set of people is appealing. Further, I particularly loved the Literati event conducted in the even semester which had events like FindMuck and Limelight, a welcome and refreshing break from the tech events of other clubs. The past and upcoming projects of this club also are interesting, including the social work being done in the nearby village. I would love to be a part of it all.
why_not_you: Like I mentioned in the above answer, IE is where I think members from various non-tech clubs in college come together. And not being a part of any of these other clubs, I might not be able to contribute significantly to further diversify the club.
core_sig_interests: Being exposed to only the coding aspect of Computer Science until a year ago, this was was a branch I chose partly because of my interest in programming and partly  because I could not picture myself in any other field. And having just began my second year here, the various non-coding aspects of this branch have not failed to capture my interest. I would love to further explore other topics and hopefully in the process chart out a well-thought out career path for myself.
aux_sig_interests:
I happened to chance upon the NITK Amateur Writers group on facebook last year, and was blown away by the stories I read there. The description said that it was an IE SIG, and I hope it isn't on it's way out. 
Also, being an animal lover, it's a sad feeling to see how dogs are generally seen to be a menace here, atleast in the girls block. Though I haven't really thought much about it, I'd like to see something being done to improve their conditions, maybe under Vriddhi.

name: Siddharth Dhananjay
about_me: I am a person who is dedicated and strives to achieve his goals. I enjoy taking up challenges and feel that I can do well in a team, as evidenced by the fact that over the summer holidays, I worked with my friends to build a website, www.thenitklife.weebly.com with the aim of providing useful information about our college to the prospective juniors.
why_ie: The Institution of Engineers is one of the most prestigious clubs a student of NITK can be a member of. It helps everyone achieve their goals and has possibly the greatest variety of SIGs of any club in this college. I feel that it breeds a competitive spirit among its members while maintaining unity and ensuring that anyone gets any desired help in their projects. I can thrive in such an environment. The best part of IE, though, which I think sets it apart from the rest, is the fact that it recognises that people can havr multiple fields of interest and consequently allows us to join multiple SIGs.
why_not_you: I usually prefer to dedicate myself to only one objective or project at a time-I don't like to handle several simultaneously.
core_sig_interests: As a student of Metallurgical and Materials Engineering, I am deeply interested in various types of materials. I am particularly interested in recent discoveries and in materials used in the automotive and aerospace industries. Regarding Code, I have always been fascinated by the ability of programmers to control the actions of a computer with just a few written lines and the application of logic.
core_sig_projects: Regarding Garage, I have begun reading about nanoparticles, especially their characterisation techniques, such as XRD, AAS and so on. Regarding Code, I participate in various coding competitions on a regular basis, such as those hosted on Codechef.
aux_sig_interests: I think there should be a fourth technical SIG specifically to deal with Materials Science. Although currently included in Garage, materials science projects are not given as much importance as Mechanical Engineering projects. Such a SIG could help introduce people to various aspects of Materials Science and introduce them to the equipment such as SEM/TEM available in our college. Members of the SIG could undertake relevant projects, possibly along the lines of those undertaken during Engineer. A possible name for the SIG could be a popular fictional metal alloy, a name known to most students, ADAMANTIUM.

name: Krishna Kinnal
about_me: I am the kind of person who loves to appreciate the world, and how it works, and I find it amazing that our human race has come so far to achieve the things that it has. Sorry to come across as cheesy, but it's hard not to get romantic about technology. why_ie: All the greatest men and women in the field of technology have one thing in common - IE. It's an internationally reputed technical society, and who wouldn't want to be a part of it ? name: Suryansh D Kumar
about_me:
I am a soldier in this army of to-be Indian engineers, whose infantry is growing at an ever increasing rate in this 21st century.

Though we all are one among a million, each one of us is also one in a million.

I am a metalhead who loves to play guitar. I also have like to play basketball, having played at KVS regionals in my 12th standard.

I love reading books, detective stories and thrilling novels being my favourite.
I'm a huge fan of Dan Brown and love his novels for blending history, technology and suspense into one power packed novel spanning 24hours.

I am good at logical reasoning and analytical thinking and like to analyse situations and statements to find out the flaws and loopholes in them.

I love using wit and sarcasm in day to day conversations, and add spice to them with a touch of drama.

I have a somewhat eidetic memory and am good at remembering facts, figures, dates and numbers for years together. 

I am also a huge fan of ASOIAF by GRRM and have invested the summer trying to find all I can about the series, and have formulated a few theories of mine as to what will happen in the next two books.

I did my Industrial Training this Summer in an IIT Bombay Startup called Wegilant, which is a cyber security firm. There I learnt the ways and methods of ethical hacking and why it is important to have a thourough knowledge about the gadgets we use, in today's age.
why_ie:
IE, apart from being one of the exclusive clubs in NITK , gives us the opportunity to meet and interact with like minded individuals, and gives us the chance to work with them as a team.

Working on tasks with experts of different technical backgrounds would  be a very fruitful experience.

IE would enable us to play around and work on the basic laws of electronics, and give a platform to make our ideas to become real
why_not_you:
If you are someone who gets offended by frequent sarcastic and frank remarks, then you shouldn't choose me.

Also, if you do not like geeky jokes, or a sudden overdose of facts at random times pisses you off, then maybe you should not choose me.
core_sig_interests:
In this era of gadgets, where a knowledge of electronics is as important as that of basic English, it is of paramount importance that one attains a basic level of understanding and a certain expertise in the working of electronic gadgets.

Hacking was something which had caught my attention since a very young age, as it catered to my inquistive investigative mind and at the same time also to my love for computers. Though I am not an expert, but I would really like to expand my knowledge base in Hacking and coding.

Coding fascinates me as it makes me come up with logical solutions to real life interesting problems.

Though I am not an expert, but I would really like to expand my knowledge base, and tricks artillery in Hacking and coding.
core_sig_projects:
I spent my summer learning Ethical Hacking, and realised its a very wide field which needs a lot of time to become an expert into.

Apart from that , I spend some of my time studying Networking Concepts and the working of Internet.

I also sometimes attempt solving basic coding problems and studying algorithms and how they make our job simpler
aux_sig_interests:
A new SIG, along the lines of Vriddhi should be dedicated towards educating people of the weaker sections of the society and helping them acquire basic computer skills, which they have not been able to acquire because of lack of opportunity or exposure.

Helping these students inculcate hobbies, develop taste for music and coach them in sports would of great help to them
